            . I am an officer. I was sent for: the prisoner said he was very sorry.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he had a paralytic stoke, and which had partly deprived him of the use of his intellects.</p>
               <p>JURY to MR. BARRETT (clerk of the papers). Q. Is there any truth in this statement? A. He has been much afflicted, and has been in the workhouse; I have not seen any change in him with respect to his faculties; but he has stated that he was better.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 45.</p>
